-- Russia and Italy to Collaborate on Piombino Steel Plant Sold By Severstal
-- Flavia Krause-Jackson
-- 2010-07-23T12:49:44Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-23/russia-and-italy-to-collaborate-on-piombino-steel-plant-sold-by-severstal.html

          
          
             Italian Prime Minister Silvio
Berlusconi said today he will collaborate with Russia on the
future of a steel plant in Piombino, Tuscany.  
 OAO Severstal sold a controlling stake in the Lucchini SpA
steel plant. Severstal, which still owns a stake in Lucchini,
sold a controlling stake in the steel company to its Chief
Executive Officer Alexei Mordashov.  
 Berlusconi spoke at a news conference in Rome with his
Russian counterpart.  
          
          


  


        